<!--
    Demo Task 10 - Preliminary fact-check complete (Closed / Review)
    ====================================================================

    Synthetic seed record for the case-management POC scoped application.
    This file (with sibling task 09) was added in response to the QA
    Checkpoint 10 MINOR finding documenting that AAP Section 0.3.1's
    LITERAL requirement -

        "at least one open and one closed task per demo case in
         `In Progress` or `Pending` state, to exercise the
         'all-tasks-closed' gate"

    - was satisfied for case 03 (which carries one Open + one Closed
    task), but NOT for case 04 (Pending) and case 08 (In Progress),
    each of which carried only non-Closed tasks. Sibling task 09
    closes the equivalent gap for case 04.

    THIS task (Demo Task 10) closes that gap for case 08 (In Progress
    Complaint) by contributing a Closed Review task whose presence in
    the seed dataset demonstrates that the validate_resolved_transition
    subflow (../../flows/sub_flows/validate_resolved_transition.xml)
    correctly EXCLUDES Closed children when computing the non-Closed
    child count for the Complaint flow's resolve gate.

    Updated 10-task fixture matrix (tasks 09-10 added per QA
    Checkpoint 10 MINOR finding remediation):

        Task 01 - Open        / Investigation / parent case 03 (In Progress GI)
        Task 02 - Closed      / Review        / parent case 03 (In Progress GI)
        Task 03 - Open        / Follow-up     / parent case 04 (Pending GI)
        Task 04 - Closed      / Review        / parent case 05 (Resolved GI)
        Task 05 - Closed      / Other         / parent case 05 (Resolved GI)
        Task 06 - In Progress / Investigation / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)
        Task 07 - Open        / Investigation / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)
        Task 08 - Closed      / Review        / parent case 09 (Resolved Complaint)
        Task 09 - Closed      / Review        / parent case 04 (Pending GI)
        Task 10 - Closed      / Review        / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)  ## THIS FILE

    AAP literal-compliance state (per AAP Section 0.3.1):
      * Case 03 (In Progress GI):       Open (task 01) + Closed (task 02)             ✓
      * Case 04 (Pending GI):           Open (task 03) + Closed (task 09)             ✓
      * Case 08 (In Progress Complaint): Open (task 07) + Closed (task 10 - THIS)     ✓ NEW
        (also In Progress task 06; the AAP requires "at least one open
         and one closed", which is satisfied; the In Progress task 06
         is supplemental coverage of the third Choice value.)

    Lifecycle position - WHY Closed / Review / parent Complaint case
    In Progress is meaningful:
      Per AAP Section 0.5.5 the Complaint flow's resolve gate fires
      when an operator attempts to transition a Complaint case from
      In Progress to Resolved; the gate's GlideRecord query inside
      the validate_resolved_transition subflow checks for non-Closed
      children. THIS Closed Review task contributes to the case 08
      seed dataset by demonstrating that:

        (a) The subflow's GlideRecord query correctly EXCLUDES
            Closed tasks from the non-Closed child count via its
            "status != Closed" filter qualifier.
        (b) The case-08 task population is now properly mixed:
            ONE Open (task 07), ONE In Progress (task 06), ONE
            Closed (this task). Together they exercise all three
            registered case_task.status Choice values on a single
            parent case.
        (c) The blocked-resolve outcome on case 08 is unaffected:
            tasks 06 (In Progress) and 07 (Open) are still
            non-Closed, so the resolve gate's GlideRecord query
            still returns rows -> blocking error "All tasks must
            be closed before resolving this case." surfaces
            correctly. Adding a Closed task does NOT unblock the
            resolve gate; the gate blocks if ANY non-Closed task
            exists.

      The Review task type semantically captures the agent's
      preliminary fact-check activity (per AAP Section 0.5.7's
      case_task type Choice list). For a Complaint case, the
      preliminary fact-check is a typical first-stage activity
      where the agent verifies the complaint's factual basis
      before launching deeper Investigation work (per task 06's
      In Progress Investigation status: the deeper investigation
      is currently ongoing).

      The negative due_date offset (-3 days, i.e., 2026-04-28
      relative to the build-environment baseline of 2026-05-01)
      reflects that the fact-check occurred in the past. The
      my_overdue_tasks report correctly EXCLUDES this task
      because its filter requires status != Closed; this Closed
      task is excluded regardless of due_date.

    Role / cross-dependency context (per AAP Section 0.5.2):

      This task DEPENDS ON (loaded BEFORE this record):
        - The scoped application records under ../../app/
        - The case_task table at ../../tables/x_casemgmt_case_task.xml
        - All dictionary entries for case_task fields under
            ../../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_task_*.xml
        - The choice records at ../../choices/sys_choice_case_task_type.xml
            (registers "Review") and ../../choices/sys_choice_case_task_status.xml
            (registers "Closed")
        - The auto-numbering record at ../../numbers/sys_number_x_casemgmt_case_task.xml
        - The role records under ../../roles/ and ACL records under ../../acl/
        - ../users/sys_user_x_casemgmt_demo_agent.xml (referenced by <assigned_to>;
            resolved by user_name lookup)
        - ../cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_08.xml (referenced by <case>;
            resolved by number lookup)

      This task IS REFERENCED BY (loaded AFTER this record):
        - The validate_resolved_transition subflow at
            ../../flows/sub_flows/validate_resolved_transition.xml
            EXCLUDES this task from its non-Closed child count.
        - The Agent Workspace dashboard's "My Overdue Tasks" widget
            EXCLUDES this task (Closed status excluded regardless
            of due_date).

    Implementation notes:
      1. Synthetic data only; no PII. Subject text is generic
         ("Preliminary fact-check complete") and contains no
         real names, real email addresses, or real organization
         references.
      2. Sys-id-literal validation: only ONE <sys_id> element
         appears below (the task's own primary key). NO sys_id
         literals appear in any cross-reference field. The
         <case>, <assigned_to>, <sys_package>, <sys_scope>
         elements all use display_value query-by-key resolution
         (per AAP Section 0.5.2).
      3. Element ordering is strictly alphabetical within the
         <x_casemgmt_case_task> element: assigned_to, case,
         due_date, status, subject, sys_class_name, sys_created_by,
         sys_id, sys_package, sys_scope, sys_update_name, type.
         This matches every peer task file.
      4. Sys_id derivation: deterministic 32-character lowercase
         hex value computed as MD5(subject):
             MD5("Demo task 10: Preliminary fact-check complete")
             = 02f9016a4d3e21e110d84dd61ce3c566
         This matches the convention used by every peer task
         (e.g., task 02 = MD5("Demo task 02: Initial review
         complete") = 949c29a044d9fd7468ddf410173ef684).
      5. Audit fields: <sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by> for
         consistent repeatable timestamps across re-imports.
      6. Choice value spelling: "Closed" (Title Case "C") and
         "Review" (Title Case "R") match the registered choice
         values verbatim.
      7. Audit-trail consideration: this task's parent case
         (CASE0000008) is currently in In Progress status. The
         fact that a Closed Review task exists for this case
         correctly models a real-world workflow: an agent
         performs a PRELIMINARY FACT-CHECK (this Closed task)
         and a DEEPER INVESTIGATION (task 06, In Progress
         Investigation), and a WITNESS INTERVIEW PREP step
         (task 07, Open Investigation). The combination
         demonstrates the natural progression of complaint
         handling from completed early activities to ongoing
         and not-yet-started later activities.
-->
